subject: p19907884
Findings: Interval removal of a right-sided internal jugular central venous line. Multiple metallic clips overlying the superior mediastinum are unchanged in position. Lung volumes remain low leading to crowding of the bronchovascular structures. There is no evidence of focal consolidation, pleural effusion, pneumothorax, or pulmonary edema. The cardiomediastinal silhouette is within normal limits.
Impression: No evidence of acute cardiopulmonary process.
